  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "SI4732 DESIGN NOTES:\n\n1) VDD = 1.8V (use U2B MIC5504-1.8 or NCP702, input from 3V3_ANALOG)\n   VDDO = 3.3V (I/O level, connect to 3V3_ANALOG directly)\n   VA   = 3.3V (analog supply, connect to 3V3_ANALOG)\n\n2) Crystal X1: 32.768kHz, 12.5pF load capacitance\n   C6/C7 = 12pF C0G (adjust if crystal specifies different CL)\n   Keep crystal traces short, away from RF and digital signals\n\n3) FM antenna: J1 SMA → L1(270nH choke) → C12(100nF AC couple) → FMIN\n   AM antenna: J2 SMA → L2(1uH choke) → C11(100nF AC couple) → AMIN\n   Antenna traces: 50Ω microstrip, no via, no sharp bends\n\n4) I2C: shared with ES7243E ADC\n   Address: 0x11 (SDIO low at power-up) or 0x63 (SDIO high)\n   Pull-ups: R3/R4 = 4.7kΩ to 3V3_ANALOG\n\n5) RESET: active-low, pulled up 10kΩ (R5) to 3V3_ANALOG\n   SI_RESET driven by ESP32-WROVER-E GPIO27\n\n6) GPO1 (pin10): firmware uses setGpioCtl() to control MUTE\n   Drives the AUDIO_MUTE GPIO for the analog mute circuit\n\n7) Audio output: LOUT/ROUT are analog single-ended ~0.5Vpp\n   AC coupled via 4.7uF electrolytic or X5R ceramic\n   Split: one path → ES7243E ADC (for BT), one path → power amp (speaker)"
    (at 210 100)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
